    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Remove the printed packaging, casing and clips from your <strong>haggis</strong></p><p>Divide and shape the <strong>haggis </strong>into one log per person</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-haggis-balmoral-chicken-with-whisky-sauce/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>chicken</strong> to a clean chopping board, cover with <strong>cling film</strong> and bash with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> until flattened to approx. 1cm thickness</p><p>Wrap the <strong>flattened chicken </strong>around the <strong>haggis log[s]</strong>, then wrap your <strong>smoked streaky bacon </strong>around everything<strong> </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>Balmoral chicken</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-haggis-balmoral-chicken-with-whisky-sauce/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>Balmoral chicken </strong>to one side of a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 30-35 min or until the bacon is lightly brown</p><p>Meanwhile, boil a full kettle and peel your <strong>potatoes</strong> and chop them into large, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Peel and finely chop your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-haggis-balmoral-chicken-with-whisky-sauce/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>potatoes</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender</p><p>Once done, drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p><p>Return the potatoes to a low heat with a small knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a splash of <strong>milk</strong>, season with a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong> and mash until smooth and keep warm until serving</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-haggis-balmoral-chicken-with-whisky-sauce/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are cooking, wash your <strong>spring</strong> <strong>greens</strong> then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Rip the leaves off your <strong>spring greens</strong>, discard the tough stalks, then layer the leaves over each other, roll them up and slice into thin strips</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-haggis-balmoral-chicken-with-whisky-sauce/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>spring</strong> <strong>greens</strong> to a large piece of <strong>tin</strong> <strong>foil</strong> (or two!) with a large splash of <strong>cold</strong> <strong>water</strong> and a little <strong>butter</strong>, scrunch the foil around the spring greens to form a tightly sealed parcel</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Make 2 separate parcels</p><p>Once the chicken has had 30 min, remove the tray[s] from the oven and add the <strong>foil parcel[s]</strong> to the other side of the tray[s], then return the tray[s] to the oven for a final 10-12 min or until the spring greens are tender and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 these are your <strong>buttery greens and Balmoral chicken</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-haggis-balmoral-chicken-with-whisky-sauce/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is cooking, reboil half a kettle</p><p>Heat a small pot over a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, once hot, add the <strong>chopped shallot </strong>and <strong>chopped garlic,</strong> then cook for 1-2 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened, add 1 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp] </span><strong>flour </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Add 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[130ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[170ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> with your <strong>whisky paste</strong>,<strong> clotted cream</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>pepper</strong>, then cook for 3-4 min or until thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>whisky sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-haggis-balmoral-chicken-with-whisky-sauce/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>Balmoral chicken </strong>on a clean board</p><p>Serve the <strong>sliced Balmoral chicken </strong>with the <strong>mash </strong>and <strong>buttery greens </strong>to the side</p><p>Pour over the <strong>whisky sauce</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
